body:
It is probably related to the vendor directory. Let's see if we can fix it
for the release candidate.

On 19 January 2016 at 09:45, Peter Harris <notifications@github.com> wrote:

> In the MSI, hpack.a has a timestamp of 2016-01-14 00:25:12. hpack.go has a
> timestamp of 2016-01-14 00:24:08. These timestamps appear to be preserved
> by the installer (although the output of "dir" truncates the seconds, so
> I'm not absolutely sure about seconds).
>
> Hmm. That's over a minute. So it's probably something else. Sorry for the
> red herring.
